Clark Equipment Co said it haspurchased 1,339,000 shares of its common stock from an investorgroup led by Arthur M. Goldberg for 26.375 dlrs a share.    It said the purchase reduces the number of shares of Clarkcommon stock to be purchased under its stock repurchase planannounced March 10. At the time the company said it would buyback 3.0 mln shares, or 16 pct of the outstanding stock.     Clark Equipment also said the investor group agreed toenter into a standstill agreement which prohibits members ofthe group from purchasing shares of voting securities of Clarkfor 10 years. Reuter&#3;